Question:
Find and print the smallest value.
Input:
List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(8, 2, 13, 6);

Solution:-
Java 8 Streams find the minimum using the min(Comparator) terminal operation on a stream of Integer values. For input [8, 2, 13, 6], it prints 2.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream the list via stream(). 
Call min(Comparator.naturalOrder()) to get Optional<Integer> with smallest by natural order.
Use ifPresent(System.out::println) to print if present.
​
#Complete Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.Comparator;
import java.util.List;

public class FindMinPrint {
    public static void findAndPrintMin(List<Integer> numbers) {
        numbers.stream()
               .min(Comparator.naturalOrder())
               .ifPresent(System.out::println);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(8, 2, 13, 6);
        findAndPrintMin(list);
    }
}

Prints 2. Optional.ifPresent safe; no .get() NPE risk.
​
#Thought Process
min(comparator) reduces to smallest via comparisons; natural order ascending for Integer (smallest first). Optional handles empty. Alternatives: reduce(Integer::min), mapToInt().min(); min most direct.
​
#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: Empty Optional, nothing prints.​
Null list: NPE on stream(); null-check.
Null elements: NPE on comparison; filter Objects::nonNull.​
Single element: Returns it.
All equals: Returns any.
Negatives/large: Handles full int range.
